Ian,

That looks to me like it will get most of what you want.  You might want 
to drop the public requirement: that would give you a warning if tests 
you expected to run were skipped because their class was accidentally 
non-public.  Although, we do the same in Eclipse.

Here&#39;s the code that Eclipse uses--you&#39;ll have to adapt, since this uses 
Eclipse&#39;s own Java model.

Share and Enjoy,

    David Saff

